{"type":"message","id":"07ac1625","parentId":"8744905f","timestamp":"2026-03-04T23:30:08.638Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the learnings. Let me analyze them for:\n\n1. **Duplicates/Merge candidates** - Same or very similar learnings across files\n2. **Promotions** - Durable rules worth adding to AGENTS.md\n3. **Keep** - Low-signal learnings worth preserving but not promoting\n4. **Propose Delete** - Obsolete learnings\n\nLet me analyze each learning:\n\n1. **2026-03-04__imperium-core-validation.md**\n   - About: validation of Imperium Core workspace, 6 acceptance tests passed\n   - This documents successful baseline - NOT a rule, just a record of success\n   - Keep: important regression baseline for the builder\n\n2. **2026-03-04__memory-curator-bootstrap-pass.md**\n   - About: Memory Curator bootstrap validation (4/4 tests passed)\n   - Contains: promotion rules logic (\"distinguishes AGENTS.md (global) from MEMORY.md (preferences)\")\n   - This could be promoted! It documents the correct promotion logic\n\n3. **2026-03-04__repo-guardian-test-semantics.md**\n   - About: fixing test semantics in Repo Guardian\n   - Contains: \"Separated validator behavior result from workspace compliance result\"\n   - This is important - could be promoted as a general validation principle\n\n4. **2026-03-04__research-scout-bootstrap-pass.md**\n   - About: Research Scout bootstrap validation (4/4 tests passed)\n   - Contains: notes about web_search unavailable, web_fetch works\n   - Keep: documents tool availability constraints\n\n**Duplicates:**\n- None directly duplicate. The \"bootstrap pass\" learnings are similar in structure but cover different agents.\n\n**Promotions (max 3):**\n1. From memory-curator-bootstrap-pass: \"Distinguishes AGENTS.md (global) from MEMORY.md (preferences)\" - This is durable operational knowledge\n\n\n2. From repo-guardian-test-semantics: The semantic separation of validation results from compliance status is a solid principle worth institutionalizing\n3. From imperium-core-validation: The six-test baseline serves as a valuable regression framework for future validation cycles\n\nThe remaining learnings about tool availability and bootstrap results are worth preserving as operational context without needing elevation to AGENTS.md.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qpdfr9xe56u8_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"minimax/minimax-m2.5:free","usage":{"input":916,"output":504,"cacheRead":13484,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14904,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772666999643}}
{"type":"message","id":"b078f2f9","parentId":"07ac1625","timestamp":"2026-03-04T23:30:08.644Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qpdfr9xe56u8_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# AGENTS.md — Operating Rules (Main + Sub-agents)\n\nThis file is the cross-cutting law. Sub-agents MUST follow it.\n\n## Session start (required)\nBefore producing outputs:\n1) Read SOUL.md\n2) Read USER.md\n3) Read today's memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md (and yesterday if present)\n4) If MAIN PRIVATE SESSION: read MEMORY.md if present\n5) Scan .learnings/ for relevant recent lessons (last ~10 entries if large)\n\n## Default guardrails\n- Ask-before-destructive: no destructive ops (delete/overwrite/force-push) without explicit approval + rollback plan.\n- Prefer trash over rm. Prefer \"preview/dry-run\" modes.\n- Ask-before-outbound: never send messages (email/DM/etc.) without explicit approval of final text.\n- Stop-on-CLI-error: if a command fails or flags are unknown, stop and run --help (or read docs), then propose corrected command.\n- No secrets: never store or paste credentials/tokens/keys into repo files, logs, or chat.\n- Minimize data exposure: do not dump large directory listings or private data; summarize.\n\n## Group chat etiquette\n- Don't claim to be the user.\n- Don't leak private memory or user data.\n- Only respond when adding value.\n\n## Memory workflow\n- Raw notes → memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md (append-only)\n- Curated → MEMORY.md (promote when stable/durable)\n- Learnings → .learnings/ (errors, corrections, feature requests)\n\n## Delegation protocol\nWhen spawning sub-agents:\n- Pass: goal, constraints, definition of done, relevant workspace excerpts\n- Exclude: secrets, credentials, private data\n\n## Evaluation\nFor meaningful changes, include:\n- Checklist of what was done\n- Rollback plan (how to undo)\n- Acceptance tests (3-5 prompts to validate behavior)\n\n## Imperium workflow (Build / Update / Validate)\nFor every agent build:\n1) Clarify only the minimum (mission, autonomy, surfaces/tools, memory, \"never do\", success metrics).\n2) Generate workspace files:\n   - SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, USER.md, AGENTS.md, TOOLS.md,\n   - HEARTBEAT.md, BOOTSTRAP.md, optional MEMORY.md\n3) Add acceptance tests (5–10 prompts) and a rollback note.\n4) Run a quick lint pass (manual checklist or script) to confirm guardrails exist.\n\n## Multi-agent orchestration (when complexity is non-trivial)\nSpin up sub-agents when needed:\n\n### Planner\n- Produces: plan, risks, assumptions, definition of done, acceptance tests.\n\n### Executor\n- Produces: file edits, commands (if any), change log, rollback steps.\n\n### Critic\n- Produces: verification checklist, safety audit, missing edge cases, fixes.\n\n### Delegation protocol (mandatory)\nWhen delegating, include:\n- Goal + definition of done\n- Constraints: ask-before-destructive, ask-before-outbound, no secrets\n- Relevant excerpts from USER.md + guardrails above\n- Output format required\n- What *not* to do\n\n## Pi memory workflow (promotion rules)\n- Write raw events/decisions to memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md.\n- Only promote durable items to MEMORY.md:\n  - stable preferences, stable constraints, ongoing projects, \"never do\"\n- Learnings go to .learnings/ first, then promoted into:\n  - AGENTS.md if it's a global operational rule\n  - MEMORY.md if it's specific to Ollie\n\n## Evaluation loop (required for deliverables)\nEvery meaningful output must include:\n- Quick self-checklist\n- Acceptance tests (prompts)\n- Rollback / undo guidance\n- \"What could go wrong\" (1–3 bullets)\n\n## Preflight Checklist (before delivering a workspace)\nConfirm the agent workspace includes:\n- SOUL.md defining tone and safety boundaries\n- USER.md with user preferences and timezone\n- AGENTS.md with guardrails\n- Ask-before-outbound rule\n- Ask-before-destructive rule\n- Stop-on-CLI-error rule\n- Pi memory workflow (daily log + curated memory)\n- Acceptance tests (≥5 prompts)\n- Rollback instructions\nIf any item is missing, fix before delivery.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772667008641}}
{"type":"message","id":"08e8fdd2","parentId":"b078f2f9","timestamp":"2026-03-04T23:30:23.375Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need to produce the memory sweep analysis. Let me analyze:\n\n**Learnings scanned:** 4 files in .learnings/\n\n1. **2026-03-04__imperium-core-validation.md** - Records successful validation of Imperium Core with 6 acceptance tests. Notes that no rule changes needed.\n\n2. **2026-03-04__memory-curator-bootstrap-pass.md** - Records Memory Curator bootstrap success (4/4 tests). Notes it's ready for registration.\n\n3. **2026-03-04__repo-guardian-test-semantics.md** - Records correction of test semantics (separating validator behavior from workspace compliance). Important procedural learning.\n\n4. **2026-03-04__research-scout-bootstrap-pass.md** - Records Research Scout bootstrap success (4/4 tests). Notes web_search unavailable but web_fetch works.\n\n**Analysis:**\n\n**Duplicates:** None detected. Each file covers distinct topics (validation baseline, Memory Curator bootstrap, test semantics fix, Research Scout bootstrap).\n\n**Promotion candidates:**\nLooking at what could be promoted to AGENTS.md:\n\n1. **Repo Guardian Test Semantics** - This is about how to run validation tests. It's a specific operational procedure, not a general rule. Could be useful as a general principle but it's very specific to Repo Guardian workflow.\n\n2. **Imperium Core Validation** - This is about keeping regression tests. The key insight is: \"Reuse the same 6 prompts whenever: AGENTS.md changes, new builder skills are added, orchestration rules change.\" This is actually useful - it's a workflow rule about regression testing.\n\n3. The bootstrap passes are just recording success - not actionable rules.\n\nLooking at AGENTS.md, it already has:\n- Preflight Checklist (very similar to what's in the validation learning)\n- Evaluation loop (similar to acceptance tests requirement)\n\nThe only thing I see that could be promoted is the regression test concept from imperium-core-validation.md, but it's already partially covered by existing rules.\n\n\nAll four files represent meaningful operational knowledge - validation baselines, bootstrap success, test semantics corrections, and regression testing principles. None are truly redundant or low-signal enough to warrant removal. The bootstrap records serve as important documentation of successful agent builds, while the test semantics fix is a substantive procedural improvement. No deletions needed.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n• **total learnings scanned:** 4\n• **duplicates detected:** 0\n• **promotion candidates:** 1\n\n---\n\n### Promote\n\n| File | Snippet |\n|------|---------|\n| `2026-03-04__imperium-core-validation.md` | **Regression Tests**: \"Reuse the same 6 prompts whenever: AGENTS.md changes, new builder skills are added, orchestration rules change\" |\n\n**Rationale:** This is a durable operational rule already implied by the Evaluation loop in AGENTS.md but not explicitly stated. Adding a regression testing rule would formalize it.\n\n---\n\n### Merge\n\nNo merge candidates — each learning covers a distinct topic.\n\n---\n\n### Keep\n\n| File | Reason |\n|------|--------|\n| `2026-03-04__imperium-core-validation.md` | Establishes baseline for Imperium Core; documents the 6 acceptance tests. Useful for regression detection. |\n| `2026-03-04__memory-curator-bootstrap-pass.md` | Documents Memory Curator bootstrap success; includes evidence that guardrails work. |\n| `2026-03-04__repo-guardian-test-semantics.md` | Important procedural correction — separates validator behavior from workspace compliance. Could inform future test framework improvements. |\n| `2026-03-04__research-scout-bootstrap-pass.md` | Documents Research Scout bootstrap; notes web_search unavailable, web_fetch works — useful environment context. |\n\n---\n\n### Propose Delete\n\nNone — all 4 learnings have signal:\n- 2 are bootstrap success records (evidence of working agents)\n- 1 is a validation baseline (regression reference)\n- 1 is a procedural correction (test semantics)\n\n---\n\n### Note on Promotion Limit\n\nOnly 1 promotion candidate identified (regression tests rule). This is under the 3-max limit. The other learnings are valuable but either:\n- Already covered by existing AGENTS.md rules (preflight checklist, evaluation loop)\n- Too specific to a single agent to warrant global elevation"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"minimax/minimax-m2.5:free","usage":{"input":934,"output":889,"cacheRead":14396,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16219,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772667008644}}
